<title>UK: Triad shares slump after growth warning.</title>
<headline>Triad shares slump after growth warning.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-02-10</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Triad Group Plc slumped on Monday after the firm said delays in finalising some of its contracts mean that growth for the year to March 1997 is unlikely to meet market expectations.</p>
<p>It said that current trading was strong and that the benefit of new contracts would be felt in the coming months.</p>
<p>Triad also announced that it has appointed Mira Makar chief executive and Alistair Fulton non-executive chairman. It added that Tim Eglen has resigned his directorship.</p>
<p>By 0825 GMT, shares in Triad had lost 36 pence to stand at 237-1/2 pence.</p>
